article.headline: Chicago St 74, Oral Roberts 66
article.story: CHICAGO (AP) -- Craig Franklin scored 28 points as Chicago State defeated Oral Roberts 74-66 on Saturday. Tony Weeden added 12 points for Chicago State (4-14, 3-2 Mid-Continent Conference). Ken Tutt led Oral Roberts (12-5, 5-1) with 27 points, and Josh Atkinson added 10 points. No other Oral Roberts player reached double figures. The game was tied at 25 at the half, but Chicago State pulled away, outscoring Oral Roberts by eight in the second half. The teams finished the game almost even in a number of statistical categories. For example, Chicago State shot 50 percent from the field while Oral Roberts hit 49.1 percent. Chicago State pulled down 32 rebounds, compared to 30 for Oral Roberts. And both teams had 16 assists. Chicago State did shoot considerably better from behind the 3-point line, making 7-of-13 shots compared to 6-of-20 for Oral Roberts.
